@startuml TWRobotAccount_MainFlow
title TW Robot Account - Main Flow

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam handwritten false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam titleFontSize 16
skinparam titleFontStyle bold

|JobService|
start
:POST /api/classificationJobs/robotTWClassification;
note right
  Parameters:
  - batchExternalSize: Batch size for external push
  - batchInternalSize: Batch size for PA insertion
  
  Ex: batchExternalSize = 1000, batchInternalSize = 5000
end note

:ScanningTWRobotAccount(batchExternalSize, batchInternalSize);
:Validate batch sizes > 0;

if (Valid?) then (yes)
  :InsertTWRobot();
else (no)
  :Log Error - Invalid Batch Size;
  stop
endif

|Service Layer|
:Start();
note right
  **Initialize TWRobotUserViewEntity**:
  - RobotUsers: Empty list
  - MaxTimestamp: 0
end note

:GetLastTimespan();
note right
  **Get Last Scanned Timespan**:
  
  System Parameter:
  - Key: RobotAccountLastScannedTime
  - Value: Last timestamp (long)
  
  **Purpose**:
  - Time-based pagination
  - Get robots since last scan
  - Incremental processing
end note

:GetTWRobotUser();
note right
  **Get TW Robot Customers**:
  
  1. Query TW System:
     - FROM TW Robot Database
     - WHERE Timestamp > @lastScannedTimespan
     - TW system detected robots
     - ORDER BY Timestamp
  
  **Source**: TW (Taiwan) System ⭐
  
  **Returns**: TWRobotUserViewEntity
  - RobotUsers[] (CustId, Counter)
  - MaxTimestamp (for pagination)
  
  **TW Detection Criteria**:
  - Taiwan-specific robot rules
  - Manual/rule-based detection
  - Regional focus (Taiwan market)
  - Historical data analysis
end note

if (Has robot users?) then (yes)
  :GetCustomerRole();
  note right
    **Enrich with Customer Role**:
    
    1. Extract CustIDs from RobotUsers
    2. Convert to comma-separated string
    3. Query Customer Role:
       - Get RoleID for each CustID
       - 1 = Member, Others = Agency
    4. Update RobotUsers with RoleID
    
    **Purpose**:
    - Separate Member vs Agency
    - Different processing paths
    - Agency → Agency API
    - Member → Direct PA insert
  end note

  :GetRobotUserCategoryId();
  note right
    **Get Robot Category**:
    
    Query: GetCategoryByCategoryTypeName
    - CategoryTypeName: "ROBOTUSER"
    - Returns: CategoryID for Robot
    
    **Validation**:
    - If null → Log error
    - Robot category must exist
    - Used for all robot PA inserts
  end note

  :InsertTWRobotPackage();
  note right
    **Two-Path Processing** ⭐:
    
    1. **Agency Robots** (RoleID != 1):
       - Call Agency API
       - Batch insert via external endpoint
       - Different handling
    
    2. **Member Robots** (RoleID == 1):
       - Direct PA insert
       - Batch processing with chunks
       - Push to MainDB
    
    **Sequential Processing**:
    - Agency first, then Member
    - If Agency fails → stop
    - If Member fails → stop
  end note

  partition "Agency Robot Processing" {
    :Filter: RoleID != 1 (Agency);
    
    if (Has agency robots?) then (yes)
      :Log input data;
      
      :Build InsertTWAgencyRobotModel;
      
      :Call Agency API (POST);
      note right
        **Agency API Call**:
        - Endpoint: agencyApiUrl + /InsertTWRobotAgency
        - Parameters:
          * Robots: Agency robot list
          * InternalSize: batch size
          * ExternalBatchSize: external batch
          * FromFlow: CTSServices
        
        **API handles**:
        - Agency-specific PA insert
        - External routing
        - Special agency rules
      end note

      if (API failed?) then (yes)
        :Return false;
        stop
      endif
    else (no)
      note right
        No agency robots
        Skip agency processing
      end note
    endif
  }

  partition "Member Robot Processing" {
    :Filter: RoleID == 1 (Member);
    
    if (Has member robots?) then (yes)
      :Chunk by batchInternalSize;
      
      repeat
        :Process member chunk;
        
        :Log input data;
        
        :Transform to InsertProblemAccountEntity;
        note right
          **TWRobotUserEntity → InsertProblemAccountEntity**:
          
          new InsertProblemAccountEntity(robot, robotCategoryId)
          {
            CustID: robot.CustId,
            CategoryID: robotCategoryId,
            RoleID: robot.RoleID,
            // ... robot-specific fields
          }
        end note

        :InsertProblemAccountPackage();
        note right
          **Insert Robot PA Classification**:
          - FunctionId: RobotUserJob
          - CCInputFlow: InsertPACategory
          - Insert into CTSCustomerClassification
          - Robot category
          - Returns: Inserted CustIDs
          
          **Inherited Method** from ProblemAccountServices
        end note

        :PushExternalPackageByCustId();
        note right
          **Push to MainDB** (External):
          - Input: Inserted CustIDs
          - Parameters: pushConfig
            * RoleGroup: Member
            * IsUpdateDangerToMainDB: true
            * IsSyncAFCData: false (no AFC for robots)
          - Makes robot classification visible
        end note

        if (Push failed?) then (yes)
          :Return false;
          stop
        endif

        :Thread.Sleep(RobotUsers_SleepTimes);
        note right
          **Throttling** ⭐:
          - Sleep between chunks
          - Prevents database overload
          - Prevents API overload
          - Smooth processing
        end note

      repeat while (More member chunks?) is (yes)
      -> no;
    else (no)
      note right
        No member robots
        Skip member processing
      end note
    endif
  }

  |System Parameters|
  :UpdateLastTimespan();
  note right
    **Update System Parameter**:
    - Key: RobotAccountLastScannedTime
    - Value: robotInfo.MaxTimestamp
    
    **Enables**:
    - Next run starts from last timestamp
    - Time-based pagination
    - No re-processing
    - Incremental scanning
  end note

else (no)
  note right
    **No TW robot users**:
    All robots processed
    or no new robots detected
  end note
endif

|JobService|
:Complete;
note right
  **Job Completion**:
  All TW-detected robots processed
  System parameter updated to latest timestamp
  Ready for next job run
end note

note right
  **Key Characteristics**:
  
  1. **TW System Detection Source** ⭐:
     - Taiwan-based robot detection
     - Manual/rule-based detection
     - Regional focus
     - Historical data analysis
  
  2. **Time-Based Pagination**:
     - Uses Timestamp for incremental processing
     - WHERE Timestamp > @lastScannedTimespan
     - System parameter persisted
  
  3. **Dual-Path Processing** ⭐:
     - **Agency**: Via Agency API (special handling)
     - **Member**: Direct PA insert + Push MainDB
     - Sequential processing
  
  4. **5-Step Fluent Chain**:
     - Start → GetLastTimespan → GetTWRobotUser
     - → GetCustomerRole → GetRobotUserCategoryId
     - → InsertTWRobotPackage
  
  5. **Batch Processing with Throttling**:
     - Chunk by internalSize (Member only)
     - Sleep between chunks ⭐
     - Prevents overload
  
  6. **Long Timeout**:
     - SP timeout: 900 seconds (15 minutes)
     - Complex TW system query
     - Large dataset possible
  
  **TW Robot Detection**:
  - Source: TW (Taiwan) System
  - Rule-based detection
  - Taiwan market specific
  - Manual review integration
end note

stop

@enduml

